Our Services

Our Services
Since our founding in 1979, we have grown from a small think tank in a single apartment into a global firm spanning 12 offices on three continents. And while our impact on health care (and education) has multiplied over the decades, our commitment to members hasn't changed. 
Through our membership model, we collaborate with executives and their teams to find and implement the best solutions to their toughest challenges. We offer:

Research: Proven, actionable insights inspired by health care’s most progressive organizations.

Technology: Analytics platforms that surface opportunities, hardwire best practices, and accelerate progress.

Consulting: Seasoned experts providing strategic, customized support.

Learn more about how we’re helping members transform their strategy, care delivery, and operations—and why organizations look to us as a strategic partner.




Our Members

Our Members
We partner with more than 252,000 leaders in more than 4,400 health care organizations. It's an honor to serve the world's most progressive organizations in this sector—a mission above commerce.
Our U.S. members include:

All of the 2015 U.S. News & World Report honor roll hospitals

96% of U.S. News & World Report's 2015 "Best Hospitals"

9,500 CEOs and COOs

In addition, for more than two decades, we have served health care organizations and institutions beyond the borders of the United States through our Advisory Board International memberships.




Our Staff

Our Staff
We employ a diverse group of talented, curious, engaged individuals—people who want fast-paced opportunities that make real change in industries that matter to everyone. By supporting their growth, we nurture long, dynamic careers and position our employees to make a real difference. 
It all starts with our culture. From recent graduates to seasoned experts and senior executives, our staff embodies the principles that have guided The Advisory Board Company since its inception.
We also support our staff for the long-haul, offering numerous professional and personal development opportunities. From training sessions to community service activities, career coaching, comprehensive benefits, and more, we create an environment that supports employees inside and outside of work.
Learn more about career opportunities on The Advisory Board Company website . 












