Health Care Advisory Board
Strategic guidance in a changing industry


With purchasers demanding more affordable care, how can you restructure operations to lower costs? And how—and where—can you build out population health capabilities at the same time?
Learn how we give health system executives the tools and insights needed for success.
Find out more about membership





Featured Resources







How will your hospital retain local control?

Download our executive guide for seven best practices you can use to lead your hospital into the future with healthy margins and continued independence.
Download the Guide 



Lessons from High-Performance Medical Groups at Independent Hospitals

While employment is a versatile model, a contract alone does not guarantee a successful arrangement. Learn the 15 core attributes high-performing groups tend to exhibit and how to replicate them.
Download the Briefing  











What every health care executive needs to know

Health care is entering the next era of reform, which will center on transforming care delivery to meet two market trends: population health and consumerism. How will your organization respond?
Get 12 insights 



Build your consumer-oriented ambulatory network

Patients are behaving like consumers. That means they want services that are affordable, accessible, and customized to their preferences and needs. Here's how to profitably meet those demands.
Read the briefing 











Hear From Our Experts









5 must-have upgrades for the consumer-focused health system

If they hope to grow, organizations must build long-term durable relationships with their customers. See five upgrades health systems should make to succeed in this new era of health care.
Download the infographic 









Why system integration is more important than ever

Hospital mergers are happening all over the country, and when two groups come together, there's always going to be friction. The problems that come with hospital mergers can't be solved unless everyone wants to solve them.
Watch the video 









How a top hospital helps patients manage their asthma

Learn how IMPACT DC, a program of Children's National Medical Center, helps providers more effectively educate patients and caregivers about living with asthma.
Watch the video 









From Medicare ACO to Medicare Advantage

Many of the population health early adopters that tried Medicare Shared Savings are now starting to aggressively add lives through Medicare Advantage. Here's why.
